Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
The project is located on McCarran Blvd, Reno’s only ring road. This major arterial is one of the City’s main commuter routes, and has a high daily traffic count of 36,000 cars per day. The subject property is strategically positioned near the new southeast connector (Veterans Parkway), which lies to the east, and connects south Reno
to Interstate 80, via Rock Blvd. 

This new development will be a mixed use project of retail, fast casual and fast foods restaurants,
automotive and industrial. The main entrance to the Park at McCarran is at the fully signalized intersection of Mill Street and McCarran Blvd, and will open up to roughly 40,000 SF of freestanding and multi-tenant retail user with drive-through. In addition, a fuel/convenience store and automotive user will round out the tenant mix. A one (1.4) million square foot industrial park is slated for construction directly
behind the retail portion of the development, which will create 25,000 vehicular trips per day and provide
an employment base of over 1,000 daytime workers.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
The Reno Experience District is deep-rooted in the history of Reno. The project is located on the busy intersection of Plumb Lane and South Virginia Street at the southern entrance to Reno’s midtown District.
Plumb Lane is a main commuter route that links the residences in west Reno to Interstate 580 and the
Reno/Tahoe International Airport. South Virginia street is Reno’s main arterial, connecting the University of Nevada to the North and the dominant Meadowood retail trade area to the South.

Serves a daytime population of 21,3033 within a one mile radius, frontage on S. Virginia Street, Reno's busiest arterial. Located within the Meadowood Trade Area. Reno;s regional trade area enjoys low vacancy and a great mix of daytime business employees & high end residential to the west
